{{Infobox Galaxy | name = [[New General Catalogue#Index Catalogue|IC]] 3 | image = IC 3 SDSS image.jpg | image_size = 250px | caption = [[Sloan Digital Sky Survey|SDSS]] image of IC 3. | epoch = [[J2000]] | type = E0<ref name="ned">{{cite web | title=NASA/IPAC Extragalactic Database | work=Results for IC 3 | url=http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/ | accessdate=2017-08-20}}</ref> | ra = {{RA|00|12|06.1}}<ref name="ned" /> | dec = {{DEC|-00|24|55}}<ref name="ned" /> | dist_ly = 228,992,400 [[Light-year|ly]] | z = 0.018130<ref name="ned" /> | h_radial_v = 5435 km/s<ref name="ned" /> | appmag_v =14.7<ref name="ned" /> | size_v = 0.4 x 0.3<ref name="ned" /> | constellation name = [[Pisces (constellation)|Pisces]] | names = CGCG 382-32, MCG 0-1-38, NPM1G -00.0003, [[Principal Galaxies Catalogue|PGC]] 836<ref name="ned" /> |size=~ 72,188.06 ly}} '''IC 3''' is a compact [[elliptical galaxy]] located approximately 228 million [[light-years]] away<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ned.ipac.caltech.edu/cgi-bin/objsearch?objname=IC+3&extend=no&hconst=73&omegam=0.27&omegav=0.73&corr_z=1&out_csys=Equatorial&out_equinox=J2000.0&obj_sort=RA+or+Longitude&of=pre_text&zv_breaker=30000.0&list_limit=5&img_stamp=YES|title=Your NED Search Results|website=ned.ipac.caltech.edu|access-date=2017-08-20}}</ref> in the constellation of [[Pisces (constellation)|Pisces]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dso-browser.com/deep-sky/10728/ic-3/galaxy?term=IC+3|title=Galaxy IC 3 - Galaxy in Pisces Constellation · Deep Sky Objects Browser|last=Rojas|first=Sebastián García|date=|website=DSO Browser|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-08-20}}</ref> The galaxy was discovered by astronomer [[Stéphane Javelle]] on August 27, 1892.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cseligman.com/text/atlas/ic0.htm#ic3|title=Index Catalog Objects: IC 1 - 49|website=cseligman.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-08-20}}</ref>
