'''Lisa Ng''' is a [[virologist]]. In 2008, she became the first Singaporean and the first woman to win the ASEAN Young Scientist and Technologist Award.

== Biography ==
Lisa Ng earned a doctorate in [[molecular virology]] from the [[National University of Singapore]] and later worked in the [[Genome Institute of Singapore]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://medicalxpress.com/news/2015-04-cell-surface-protein-innate-immune.html | title=A cell surface protein known to regulate innate immune responses also affects the adaptive immune system | publisher=medicalxpress.com  | date=15 April 2015| accessdate=19 November 2015}}</ref> She works as an Associate Professor at the [[National University of Singapore]] and at [[Singapore Immunology Network|SIgN]] where she is the leading virologist. She is undertaking research on infectious diseases, including the Chikungungya virus, and is investigating the improvement of preparedness and prevention based on the use of vaccines and therapeutic antibodies. She has developed diagnostic kits for detecting Avian Influenza and Sars.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.asianscientist.com/2011/05/list/lisa-ng/ | title=The Ultimate List Of 15 Asian Scientists To Watch – Lisa Ng | publisher=www.asianscientist.com | work=Juliana Chan | date=15 May 2011 | accessdate=20 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://medicalxpress.com/news/2013-06-fast-simple-tropical-diseases.html | title=Fast and simple detection of tropical diseases | publisher=medicalxpress.com | date=5 June 2013 | accessdate=20 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.a-star.edu.sg/sign/Research/Principal-Investigators/tid/28/NG-Lisa-Fong-Poh.aspx | title=Lisa Fong Poh NG | publisher=star.edu.sg | accessdate=20 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | url=http://sntpost.stii.dost.gov.ph/NewPOST/JulSep2008/Filipino%20physicist.htm | title=Filipino physicist, Singaporean virologist win ASEAN Scientist and Technologist Awards | author=Framelia V. Anonas | journal=Science and Technology Post | year=2008 | month= | volume=XXVI, 3rd Quarter}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=A*STAR and Veredus Laboratories Create Market's First Lab-on-Chip for the Detection of Multiple Tropical Infectious Diseases|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-327557168.html|publisher=ACN Newswire{{Subscription required|via=HighBeam}}|accessdate=19 November 2015|date=April 25, 2013}}</ref>

